      "writtenOn": "2026-03-04T05:32:13Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Hi @ed@tanous.net We added this message to handle cases where a user uploads an invalid image during the POST operation to /redfish/v1/UpdateService/update.\n\nWith this change, the service immediately returns an error and prevents creation of a task at /redfish/v1/TaskService/Tasks/\u003cTaskId\u003e. Previously, a task would still be created, and only afterward would it fail with a 500 Internal Server Error. \n\nVerified that uploading a valid image successfully creates a task and completes the update flow as expected.\n\nVerified that uploading an invalid or corrupted image now returns an appropriate error response without creating a task.\n\nConfirmed that no /redfish/v1/TaskService/Tasks/\u003cTaskId\u003e entry is created in the failure scenario.",
